SUMMARY (the three rules)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  RULE 1 — Forking, cloning, or modifying the Software requires the
           Owner's prior WRITTEN PERMISSION. Permission is granted at
           the Owner's sole discretion.

  RULE 2 — Any USE of the Software requires PAYMENT to the Owner —
           a one-time license fee, recurring royalty, or full purchase
           of rights, as agreed in writing. This applies to ALL use,
           including personal, internal, non-profit, academic, and
           evaluation use. Permission to fork or clone (Rule 1) does
           NOT include the right to Use.

  RULE 3 — Every grant under this license requires VISIBLE ATTRIBUTION
           to "Aarohan Verma — ResearchFlow". Failure to attribute
           voids all granted rights immediately.

The formal terms below govern. The summary is for clarity, not for
legal interpretation.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
1. DEFINITIONS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   "Software" means the source code, compiled artifacts, configuration,
   prompts, prompt templates, system designs, documentation,
   architecture diagrams, database schemas, and all other content in
   this repository, plus any future updates, modifications, or
   derivative works thereof.

   "Owner" means Aarohan Verma, the sole copyright holder.

   "Permission" means a written grant from the Owner — by email
   from verma.aarohan@gmail.com or by a signed document — explicitly
   authorising a named party to perform a specific act with respect
   to the Software.

   "Use" means any of the following acts performed by any person or
   entity, in whole or in part, in any environment: executing;
   running; deploying; hosting; serving; making available over a
   network; embedding; bundling; integrating into another product;
   training, fine-tuning, or evaluating any machine-learning model
   on; or otherwise putting the Software into operational service.

   "Derivative" means any fork, clone, modification, port,
   translation, extension, plug-in, or other work based on the
   Software in whole or in part.

   "Attribution" means the visible credit specified in Section 5.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
2. PERMITTED WITHOUT PERMISSION OR PAYMENT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   You may, without seeking Permission and without paying any fee:

   (a) View the source code through a public source-hosting service
       for personal reading and reference;

   (b) Quote excerpts of the Software in reviews, criticism, academic
       commentary, or technical writing, provided you include
       Attribution as defined in Section 5.

   No other rights are granted by default.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
3. REQUIRES PERMISSION (Rule 1)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   The following acts require prior written Permission from the Owner.
   Permission may be granted or denied at the Owner's sole discretion
   and may be conditioned on any terms the Owner sees fit, including
   but not limited to fees, scope limits, and time limits.

   (a) Forking the repository to your own account or organisation;
   (b) Cloning the repository for any purpose other than personal
       reading reference;
   (c) Mirroring or republishing the source code or any portion of it;
   (d) Creating a Derivative.

   Permission granted under this section is personal,
   non-transferable, and revocable. Permission to fork, clone, or
   create a Derivative does NOT include the right to Use the
   Software or any Derivative — see Section 4.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
4. REQUIRES PERMISSION + PAYMENT (Rule 2)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   Any Use of the Software, or of any Derivative of the Software,
   requires BOTH:

   (a) Written Permission from the Owner; AND

   (b) Payment to the Owner of one of the following, as agreed in
       writing between the Use Licensee and the Owner:

           (i)   a one-time license fee for a defined scope of Use;
           (ii)  a recurring royalty (per-user, per-seat,
                 per-deployment, per-revenue, or other agreed metric);
           (iii) full purchase of the Software's IP rights at a
                 negotiated price.

   This requirement applies WITHOUT EXCEPTION to all categories of
   Use, including but not limited to:

       - Personal Use (a single individual, on a single machine,
         for non-commercial purposes);
       - Internal-business Use (a private company deployment for its
         own employees);
       - Commercial Use (offering Software functionality to paying
         or non-paying third parties);
       - Non-profit, academic, research, and evaluation Use;
       - Educational Use (classroom, course, or institutional);
       - Government Use (any governmental or quasi-governmental body).

   Permission previously granted under Section 3 (fork / clone /
   Derivative) does NOT grant any right under this Section 4. The
   right to Use is a separate right that must be separately granted
   AND separately paid for, even where the Use is of a Derivative
   created with Permission under Section 3.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
5. ATTRIBUTION (Rule 3 — REQUIRED FOR EVERY GRANT)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   Every right granted under Sections 2, 3, or 4 is conditional on
   the following Attribution being maintained at all times:

   (a) SOURCE-CODE ATTRIBUTION
       The copyright notice
              "Copyright (c) 2026 Aarohan Verma. All Rights Reserved."
       must be preserved verbatim in every source file of the
       Software or any Derivative thereof.

   (b) PRODUCT / UI ATTRIBUTION
       Any product, service, or deployment that incorporates the
       Software or a Derivative — whether public, internal, or
       personal — must display the credit:

              "Powered by ResearchFlow — © Aarohan Verma"

       or equivalent wording naming "Aarohan Verma" as the original
       author, in a location reasonably visible to the end user
       (e.g. About page, Credits screen, settings dialogue, footer,
       splash screen, or documentation index).

   (c) DOCUMENTATION ATTRIBUTION
       Any README, documentation site, technical specification, or
       internal wiki for a Derivative must credit Aarohan Verma as
       the original author of ResearchFlow and link to the
       original repository where reasonably possible.

   (d) PUBLICATION ATTRIBUTION
       Any academic paper, blog post, conference talk, podcast,
       press release, or marketing material that describes or
       references the Software's design, algorithms, or
       implementation must credit Aarohan Verma by name.

   FAILURE TO MAINTAIN ATTRIBUTION at any of the above points
   automatically and immediately voids all rights granted under
   this license without further notice. Continued Use after such
   voiding constitutes copyright infringement.

